                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5">
                        <locus target="#38r">Fol. 38r: </locus>
                        <desc>Eight Apostles. The names of the Apostles are written over their
                           heads.&#xD; Legend above (from left to right): ፊልጶስ፡ በርተሎሜዎስ፡ ቶማስ፡ ማቴዎስ፡
                           “Philip, Bartholomew, Thomas, Matthew”.&#xD; Legend below (from left to
                           right): ጴጥሮስ፡ እንድርያስ፡ ያእቆብ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ “Peter, Andrew, James,
                        John”.</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6">
                        <locus target="#38v">Fol. 38v: </locus>
                        <desc>(above) Four Apostles; (below) Archangel Michael and the donor (?).
                           The names of the Apostles are written over their heads.&#xD; The legends
                           are barely legible.&#xD; Legend above (from left to right): ታዴ[ዎ]ስ፡
                           ናትናኤል፡ ማርቆስ፡ ያዕቆብ፡ ዘእልፍ[ዮስ]፡ “Thaddeus, Nathaniel, Mark, James (the son)
                           of Alphaeus”.&#xD; Legend below (from left to right): [ቅዱስ፡] ሚካኤል፡ “Saint
                           Michael”, ወልደ፡ ሚካ{ኤ}ል፡ [ዘ]ከመ፡ [ተ]ማኅፀነ፡ [n.l.], “How Wäldä Michael
                           entrusted himself …”. </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7">
                        <locus target="#44r">Fol. 44r: </locus>
                        <desc>The Virgin and Child. Legend: ሚካኤል፡ [ማርያም፡]: ምስለ፡ ፍቁር፡ ወልዳ፡ ወገብርኤል፡
                           “Michael, [Mary] with her beloved son and Gabriel”. </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8">
                        <locus target="#44v">Fol. 44v: </locus>
                        <desc>St. George slaying the dragon. Legend: ቅዱስ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ [n.l.] ዘል[n.l.]፡
                           “Saint George …”. </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote xml:id="d9" type="band">
                        <desc>A chain of black and red right-pointing chevrons is used, at the top
                           and over cols. a and b, as decorative band on the incipit page of <ref target="#ms_i1">Text I</ref>; sometimes it (or a chain of black and
                           red dots) is also used as sections divider.</desc>
                     </decoNote>
